                    Repeated to Colonel Carter in Washington.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v10</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d397</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">397</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-02-11T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Colonel <persName type="from">George V. Underwood</persName>
                        to Lieutenant General <persName type="to">Alvan C. Gillem, Jr.</persName>,
                        at Peiping</hi>
                    <note n="21" xml:id="d397fn21">Repeated to Colonel Carter in Washington.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-11">11 February
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2067. This message is sent at the request of Doctor Stuart.</p>
                <p>The Generalissimo asked Doctor Stuart to inform you that he earnestly hoped the
                    inactivation of Executive Headquarters would not remove you from the China
                    scene. He expressed admiration for <pb facs="0725" n="715" xml:id="pg_715"/> you
                    personally and genuine appreciation for your past efforts and assistance.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
